comments: The cabin heater and the dc-to-dc converter died, with the repair cost to high for the age and value of the vehicle, so upgraded to a new Leaf. Our new-ish battery (4 years, 11,000 miles) was moved to another Leaf, see #1 on the survey.

Although I still love driving this car more than the others available to me, the battery pack is severely degraded by ~ 71%. I attribute this to being a 1st generation pack & no active cooling.  I can no longer drive it the 18 miles to work unless outside temperatures are >20°F, and instead have to substitute my gas truck, (until my Model Y or Cybertruck arrive).  Still no regrets in buying this LEAF as I enjoy driving it, and even enjoy the challenge of getting home in uncooperative weather.

My SOH seems to be varying with the seasons; in winter it goes up, in summer it goes down.  Makes it hard to really get a sense of battery degradation; pretty much have to compare to a month the previous year that had the same ambient temperatures to really get a sense of what is happening!  See my most recent blog post at http://kootenayevfamily.ca/cost-update-96000-km-and-2-5-years/ for a table of SOH data and graph of what I think is occurring.
